            <fr:taxon>Corollary</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-016M.xml" title="formal language" addr="jms-016M" type="local">formal language</fr:link> such that for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ell \geq  1]]></fr:tex>, there exists some <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-016I.xml" title="string over an alphabet" addr="jms-016I" type="local">string</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[w\in  L]]></fr:tex> satisfying <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left \lvert w\right \rvert \mathclose {}}\geq  l]]></fr:tex> such that for any decomposition <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[w=u_1 v u_2]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left \lvert u_1v\right \rvert \mathclose {}}\leq  \ell ]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v]]></fr:tex> non-empty, there exists some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u_1 v^n u_2]]></fr:tex> lies outside <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex>. Then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> is not <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-017Y.xml" title="regular language" addr="jms-017Y" type="local">regular</fr:link>.</html:p>
 
   
